\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 73. S. globulifera} Desf.,{\i  Fl. Atl.}{\b  1}: 342 (1798) (incl. {\i S. granatensis} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i S. gibraltarica }Boiss. & Reuter). Leafy shoots erect or spreading, forming a lax cushion. Leaves up to 8 × 17 mm but usually much less, semicircular in outline, rather deeply lobed with 3-7 acute lobes, glandular-hairy; petiole longer than the lamina. Summer-dormant axillary buds numerous, c. 3 mm wide, obconical, usually stalked, hairy but not white-villous. Flowering stem 7-12 cm, slender, bearing 2-7(-11) flowers. Sepals 2 mm; petals 5-7 mm, white.{\i  Limestone rocks and cliffs. S. Spain,from }4° 35'{\i  to }5° 30' {\i W.} Hs.
\par

