\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 74. S. reuteriana} Boiss., {\i Voy. Bot. Midi Esp.}{\b  2}: 730 (1845). Like {\b 73} but leaves rather larger (up to 12 × 20 mm) and with the primary lobes divided, giving 5-11 segments in all; summer-dormant buds 4-6 mm wide; flowering stem 2-5 cm, with 1-3(4) flowers; sepals 4 mm; petals 8-10 mm, with the margins deflexed near the apex, somewhat greenish-white. {\i Limestone cliffs. S. Spain }({\i mountains S. & E. of Antequera}). Hs.
\par

