\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 76. S. rigoi} Porta,{\i  Atti Accad. Agiati} ser. 2,{\b  9}: 26 (1891). Leafy shoots short, ascending, rather densely caespitose. Leaves with a long petiole, ciliate with subarachnoid hairs; lamina with 3-5 obtuse or subacute lobes furnished with shorter glandular hairs. Summer-dormant buds numerous, obovoid, stalked, their outer leaves ciliate with long white hairs. Flowering stem c. 6 cm, bearing 2 or 3 large, campanulate flowers. Petals 12-15 × 5 mm, white. •{\i  Mountains of S.E. Spain} ({\i Granada and Jaen provs.}). Hs.
\par

